Reviewed `MATERIALIZATION.md`.

The snapshot and merge model stays auditable and benchmarkable:
- snapshots and derived merges are explicit artifacts with stable ids and source lineage references
- summary filters are advisory rather than hidden correctness dependencies
- benchmark dimensions are named explicitly, including snapshot build time, bytes written, branch-local reuse ratio, merge rebuild rate, and summary-filter false-positive rate
- the contract rejects hidden in-memory mutable indexes as the semantic source of truth

This satisfies SRS-NFR-03.
